place_name: Knowledge Perk Coffee Company | Fort Mill

details.description:
Come relax in our beautiful café with indoor and outdoor seating. We offer freshly roasted coffee, cold brew, full range of expert espresso beverages, and a variety of sweet and savory pastries and bagel creations.

Thursday-Friday from 4:00pm-9:30pm, and Saturday from 6:00pm-9:30pm, we turn into Knowledge Perk "After Hours," serving coffee, original cocktails, beer, and wine.

We are a coffee roaster and beans are available onsite or via our website for retail purchase. We have immersive, engaging programs and events for our community to grow in their knowledge and enjoyment of coffee. Give us a call or visit our website for more information. Better yet, drop by to see us in person!

posts.body:
💕 Love Is in the Air 💖
Join us after your special dinner for our Valentine's Date Night at Knowledge Perk After Hours!
We're doing a lot to celebrate! You can enjoy:
- Dessert Flights (Pick 4 from 8 varieties of cheesecakes and dessert bars) 🍰
- 2 New Cocktails (Strawberries & Cream Margarita, Mudslide Martini) 🍸
- Live Music from Jeremy Goodwyne (7:30pm - 10:30pm) 🎵
- Extended hours from 6:00pm - 11:00pm
- Chocolate Cherry Lattes

Coffee. Cocktails. Beer. Wine.

☕️🥃 Knowledge Perk After Hours is celebrating its grand opening this Saturday exclusively at Knowledge Perk Fort Mill! Our new After Hours concept is currently a KP Fort Mill exclusive, and after Saturday, its weekly hours to start will be Thursday-Saturday, 6:00pm - 9:30pm. Hours will likely expand in the future!

Enjoy our hand-picked selection of beer and wine, and our new line of original Knowledge Perk cocktails!

- The Menu -

Signature Espresso Martini:
Vodka, Burn Rate Espresso, Housemade Coffee Syrup

Café Old Fashioned:
Whiskey, Coffee Liqueur, Simple Syrup, Orange Bitters, Orange Peel

Pink Russian:
Vodka, Coffee Liqueur, Strawberry Vanilla Sweet Foam, Dried Strawberry, Chocolate Shavings

True Maple Bourbon Latte:
Whiskey, Burn Rate Espresso, Maple Syrup, Steamed Milk, Nutmeg

Vanilla Chai Sour:
Spiced Rum, Oregon Chai, Vanilla Syrup, Lime Juice, Nutmeg

Campfire:
Vanilla Vodka, Bourbon Cream Liqueur, Chocolate Sauce, Milk, Crushed Graham Cracker Rim, Torched Marshmallow

Cold Brew Creamsicle:
Vodka, Orange Triple Sec Liqueur, Fresh Squeezed Orange Juice, Cold Brew Coffee, Oat Milk, Vanilla Syrup, Orange Slice

Pumpkin Shake:
Vanilla Vodka, Bourbon Cream Liqueur, Half & Half, Pumpkin Puree, Pumpkin Pie Syrup, Whipped Cream, Blended, Espresso Optional

reviews_data.review_text: Great cup of coffee and quick service, I did go in the evening
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review, Danna! Hope to see you back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Went there for their after hours event where they serve adult drinks. There was also music which was nice! Great place for impromptu date night.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review, Rob! We're glad you had a good time and hope you come back to see us again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: The coffee here is great, I recommend it. The employees are also very friendly. This is something we need in every business, especially food stores. The croissant is from somewhere else, the egg is from my kitchen. I just wanted the photo to look nice and appetizing. 🥰🤗

Knowledge Perk in Fort Mill is an absolute gem. The atmosphere is warm, welcoming, and just the right balance of calm and creative—perfect for getting work done or simply enjoying a moment of pause. I had the decaf lavender latte (extra hot), delicious. You can tell they care about the experience just as much as the coffee. Whether you’re working remotely or catching up with a friend, this is a go-to spot.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for this wonderful review, Lorelei! We hope to see you back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: We like this place very much. My kids always want hot chocolate from knowledge perk only.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're happy to hear your kids love our hot chocolate! We look forward to seeing you all back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Visiting family out of town and have been trying local coffee shops. This place was by far the best stop! The staff were very friendly and helpful with questions on their menu. Their seasonal blueberry macchiato was amazing! Lots of seating space for small and large groups. If you are looking for a new place to try, stop by here you won’t regret it!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the great review, Steven! We hope you return the next time you're in town!

reviews_data.review_text: Always enjoy to try new coffee shop locations and this time my choice fell on this one since we were visiting the area. We ordered salmon bagel and two lattes. Salmon bagel had about 1% of salmon in it, 85% cream cheese and 14% was massive chunks of purple onions mix with cream cheese. I had a bad heartburn after it. I did ask not to put it there but they said it’s all pre made mix. Coffee tasted more like water and coffee than a coffee and milk. Overall 25$ down the drain. Won’t be coming back.

Our first time in the Fort Mill location and we were very disappointed. The atmosphere wasn't there for us like the one in Rock Hill. We didn't stay long because it was freezing in there. No wonder there was hardly anybody in there on a Friday night. They have it so cold that nobody wants to stay. A coffee shop is supposed to be cozy and relaxing, not feel like a freezer. Probably won't be back.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Dear Debbie,
We appreciate all feedback, even when it’s tough to hear. It’s unfortunate that your experience at our Fort Mill location didn’t meet your expectations, especially since you seemed to enjoy our Rock Hill shop. While we strive to create a comfortable atmosphere for all guests, we also recognize that temperature preferences can vary widely. Our team is always happy to adjust when concerns are brought to our attention during a visit. I’m very confident our team would’ve been very happy to adjust temperatures if requested. It was also 20° outside, and so we understand a hot cup of coffee would certainly add to the warmness as our heaters were likely working overtime. 

That said, we’ve noticed that your reviews tend to lean toward the negative, which makes us wonder if the issue is less about our coffee shop and more about your approach to customer experiences. We take great pride in what we do, and while we may not be the right fit for everyone, we are confident in the warm and welcoming environment we provide to thousands of happy guests. I’m not sure a one star review in this case is extremely warranted, nor is it fair to us as a small business when we do a phenomenal job in so many other areas on a very consistent basis. 

If you’d like to give us another try, we’d love the opportunity to change your mind. If not, we sincerely hope you find a coffee shop that better aligns with your preferences and temperature.

Wishing you all the best,
Ryan.

reviews_data.review_text: Great frappe, nice staff, awesome atmosphere!

I've never seen a place like this. It's a full-blown coffee shop but it's also a bar. We went to see a musical act which was very good and very much enjoyed the place. I had an Irish coffee that was great.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review, Ron! We're happy you enjoyed the Irish Coffee and hope to see you back again soon to try some new drinks!

reviews_data.review_text: Coffee is always 10/10! Try the iced salted caramel latte👏👏
Always a 5 star experience! The best coffee on town!

We stopped by to grab a quick bagel and coffee. $37 for 2 coffees, 1 hot chocolate, and 2 bagels with cream cheese and one bagel sammie later. The bagels were from NY so they were pricier and not any better than I’ve had at any other bagel shop. Coffee was good, but I didn’t think it was overly amazing. The service was just alright, the baristas were not overly friendly and the girl working the counter was more interested in her friend that was there. I’d go back and get a coffee again, but I’d skip the bagel.
Great friendly service and nice atmosphere but unfortunately one of the worst lattes I’ve had around here. Borderline undrinkable
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Ahmad, thanks for visiting our café and leaving your feedback! We appreciate the kind words about our team's customer service. The latte in that photo does not meet our standards of quality and should not have been served with that much foam. We will definitely address this with our team. We apologize for your experience and hope you will give us another chance! Please send an email to fortmillgm@knowledgeperk.com so that we can make it right!

reviews_data.review_text: I got a chemex. it was nice.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review, we're happy you enjoyed your Chemex!

reviews_data.review_text: The best coffee I’ve ever tasted, especially the Toffee Crunch Iced Latte

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Cinnamon Roll and Brownie, Blueberry Muffin Top, Spinach Feta

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the 5-star review! Toffee crunch is one of our favorites too :)

reviews_data.review_text: Met a new friend for coffee to get to know each other. I got a mocha caramel latte, and it was AMAZING. They have all types of syrups for flavor, as well as milks and types of coffees to choose from. I have just found my new coffee shop❤️
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the wonderful review Nicole! We can't wait to see you back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I decided to go and try this lovely coffee shop in Fort Mill. Upon arrival I was greeted by a friendly barista then I ordered a hot Gingerbread latte which was amazing and not too sweet. The cinnamon roll with cream cheese was moist and delicious. There wasn’t a long wait and my experience there was pleasant as a new customer. Will be back soon!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review Mery! We're happy you gave us a try and look forward to seeing you back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: The new Knowledge Perk After Hours slaps. No cap.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review and for visiting us for the After Hours grand opening! Hope to see you back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Really wonderful pour over. I'm from Seattle and picky. This coffee was really satisfying. Friendly staff as well. Quality place for sure. Delicious bagel sandwiches also.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review Jenny! As someone who's enjoyed the great Seattle coffee scene myself, the review means a lot!

reviews_data.review_text:
I have drove past Knowledge Perk so many times and this weekend it was my first time visiting.
I am for sure coming back. My husband and I came for an impromptu coffee/ breakfast and we were not disappointed.
I ordered the Maple Bourbon Latte and my husband got the Au Lait. Both of the drinks were perfect. The drinks are not too sweet like other places. The sweetness was just how I like.
Goog coffee with good customer service
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review, Vicky! We hope to see you back again soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Recently started treating myself to one bought coffee a week. I prefer knowledge perk because it is close to my work, not as busy as other coffee places, and I enjoy walking inside, ordering, and waiting.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review and for choosing Knowledge Perk as your weekly treat!

reviews_data.review_text: Cute and cozy
Nice place to work with lots of room!  Clean and good WiFi
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review Keith, hope to see you back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee. Great staff. Know me by name and by order.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review Brandi! We'll see you soon :)

reviews_data.review_text: The coffee is great and they have incredibly comfortable chairs. Great place to hang out and get some work done.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review Michael! Hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I live next to this place and wanted so badly to like it, but they didn’t have vanilla, they didn’t have oat-milk (two starter pack ingredients for a coffee shop) and they forgot to make my bagel sandwich until my husband went to ask about it 10 minutes later.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for review and your feedback. We're sorry your experience didn't meet our standards of service. You unfortunately caught us on a bad day where we had some delivery issues. We do normally always have vanilla and oat milk in stock. We'd love to have you come back and give us another try. Your next vanilla oat milk latte is on us!

reviews_data.review_text: I purchased a tea which was $3.21 for a small. Which is a bit pricey I can get a whole box of tea for close to that price. . I'm not a cheapskate and I don't mind shelling out money for things I like but Dunkin Dounuts is half the price same size.  Also when I looked inside the tea it was not in a tea bag it was tea loose. This is not safe if your giving tea to a kids or the elderly they can digest the loose tea particles and choke..  I think customers should be warned of this type of brewing process.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Nora, thank you for your review and your feedback! Our tea, though loose leaf, is supposed to be properly strained and there should not be loose floating tea at the bottom of your cup. We apologize for this mistake and hope you come back to give us another chance! We would like to make this right to you, so shoot us an email at infofm@knowledgeperk.com and your next drink is on us!

reviews_data.review_text: The diced bagel sandwiches are incredible!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the great review! We're so glad you loved our bagels!

reviews_data.review_text: I like this place for a couple of reasons. They use different beans from all over the world. They have heavy cream as an option, where most only have half & half. They have real dishes, not just Togo cups. The place feels like a coffee shop, students studying, people working on their laptops, and the staff always seem happy, even when they aren’t dealing with customers.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the review and positive feedback, Jon! We hope to see you back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: This is the only place where they get the flat white right every single time, no matter who the barista is. Finding such consistent, great service is incredibly rare. It also offers a wonderful atmosphere for focusing."
great place to get work done aswell as great coffee!
First timer. The latte was pretty watery :(
Incredibly tasty coffee and espresso drinks, coupled with great service and a convenient location
This is my favorite local place for a coffee. They now have bagels!  Try the breakfast scramble!

So I'm not much of a coffee drinker, but the people and the atmosphere are amazing to be in. They open up their business to everyone and are very inviting and love their community. They allow us to host a men's fellowship every Monday morning at 7:00. We are blessed to have this business in our community. I definitely recommend
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Shaun! We love that we can provide a space for your group and others to meet. See you next week!

reviews_data.review_text: Blueberry muffin was fresh & delicious.  The coffee was freshly brewed. Great place, but pricy.
Excellent coffee, tea, and service! The snacks and treats are also delicious.

Not bad. Brewed coffee is okay. The espresso drinks are hit and miss. Lately they've been hitting properly, but the first few visits. I suspect it's training related.

They have food there, but it sells out early. I only stop in around lunch and the shelves are barren by 11
Came in two days in a row. Coffee is super yummy! Also enjoyed dining in and the snacking pastries.
Nice place and atmosphere

A DELICIOUS Lavender Latté in a MUG ,, ( holding a warm mug makes ALL the difference!) with a beautiful design 😉,, by an exceptional barista with some of my favorite people ..

🤎💜🤍🤎🤍🤎🤍🤎🤍🤎🤍🤎🤍
P.s. to the management … window blinds ( or a creative cover ? ) at the entrance facing 160 would make the corner with the couch super cozy 🙂
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review and the feedback, Jennifer! If you liked the lavender latte, you might also like the lavender honey latte next time, delicious!

reviews_data.review_text: KP has the best coffee in town! Their seasonal drink menu doesn't disappoint. The baristas are super friendly. Also, Mexico Villareal whole coffee beans FOR LIFE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Seriously good stuff!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Angel! We can't get enough of the Mexico Villareal either!

reviews_data.review_text:
I visit occasionally to catch up with a friend. We like their coffee and it's a relatively quiet place. You get a lot of street traffic noise if you sit outside. Inside is better obviously, to avoid that.

No matter what coffee you get they are usually right on the money. Also they roast their own beans at their Rock Hill location.

They have a limited amount of snacks in display case by the register and only occasionally have I ever see something that might be gluten free. So if that's you thing plan on the possibility of not having something to eat.

The furniture is ok for the most part. But the center island of stools are, to me anyway, awkward and very uncomfortable. But to be fair these are a leftover from the prior business that was there.

Stop by and have a cup, all in all it's a solid choice.
Amazing place, love the spinach feta with my coffee. #TYG #lifeisgood
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the great review! You can't go wrong with the spinach & feta!

reviews_data.review_text:
Amazing coffee! It was my first time coming in, I was visiting from out of town. Customer service was remarkable. The two workers were extremely kind, attentive, and had a great coffee knowledge 10/10.
Coffee was delicious. I really enjoyed my pour over, as well as my cortado. All around extremely consistent and tasty.
Loved the vibe of the store. Plenty of space to sit and do some work.
Will definitely be back when I’m in town next!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for the kind review, Eli! We're very proud of our great team and we look forward to seeing you again the next time you're in town!

reviews_data.review_text: Really good coffee.  Cinnamon buns were really good.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for visiting! We're happy you enjoyed our famous cinnamon rolls!

reviews_data.review_text: Amazing local coffee place! Great atmosphere and great service!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Josh!

reviews_data.review_text: The flat white was wonderful. Very relaxing and chill environment
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Drew, we're happy you enjoyed your flat white! We recommend trying one of our cortados next time, delicious!

reviews_data.review_text: Beautiful place with more perfect coffee!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the great review! We hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Good coffee shop. The vibe here is perfect for getting some work done. Coffee is solid and the space is plentiful. I like coming by here when I am around. Give it a try!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the 4-star review Joel! We would love to hear what we can do to get that 5th star from you. Hope to see you back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Awesome gingerbread latte
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're so happy you liked it! You might enjoy our Gingerbread Chai as well. Thanks for visiting and we hope to see you back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee shop
Spectacular food and service. Ordered breakfast and was delicious. Ciarra was awesome.
Did not have the advertised food.

First time experience. I showed up around 9am and ordered a Toffee Crunch latte. The baristas were friendly and my drink was made quickly. I brought my laptop as I had planned to stay and work. The shop was packed however, and the music was loud which isn’t conducive for working. The middle bar/island seating barstools are weird. They swing in/out and it’s very easy to lose your balance and slip as I did along with 2 other women who were sitting down across from me at the same time. The latte was underwhelming and was missing the rich espresso flavor I like. It tasted more like watered down coffee with flavored syrup and foam. I’m gonna stick to the Starbucks rivers and lakes I’m used to.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the review and the kind words about our team, Brittany!  We have adjusted music levels to hopefully a better level, and we acknowledge the stools... We do have plans to replace all those, they are a carry over from the original store and we are looking forward to updating them with real chairs soon! I hate that you didn't enjoy your latte, we'd love for you to come try us again.  As a small batch roaster, our espresso is a little lighter than some of the chain stores and so it can be harder to taste through the latte that has a sweeter syrup like the toffee crunch. That being said, we would love to help you find something that showcases our great espresso a little more, and we would welcome the chance to serve you again with hopefully a more positive experience! Either way, thanks for giving us a chance, we are grateful for every opportunity to earn a new customers business. Ryan

Pretty cool place. Nice atmosphere too
Excellent service and coffee!!
Great cinnamon rolls and cold brews.
The coffee is so good, the barista is amazing and the breakfast empanada’s are my favorite thing in the whole world. My husband and I love this place!
Excellent coffee and atmosphere to enjoy your drink. Nice place for a treat and a break in your day!

David, that’s how you lead the way! Veterans need and like to work! Great job brosky. You, sir, are a rockstar! Civilians DO NOT! Understand how we operate! Well done, keep leading by example. Hopefully everyone will listen to you! Finally.
Some of the best coffee I've had anywhere.  The staff is super friendly as well.

Knowledge Perk is the only place I get coffee in the area. They roast THE best coffee!

reviews_data.review_text: so presh!
Delicious coffee and the spinach feta croissant was amazing 👏
Good coffee. Better service. Just wish they had more baked goods.
Awesome coffee place! Great location, good view, calm and peaceful. Very polite staff and excellent customer service. Will be back for sure!
Great place with a cozy atmosphere

I love this coffee shop! I come here often to study. The staff is very nice and the drinks are tasty. It is decorated cutely and there are outlets in good positions. There is just one complaint I have.... It is so so cold in here. I have to bring a blanket and jacket to sit in here🥺 I still love it though❤️
Nice people and some great coffee!
Incredible cup of coffee with an even better team! Thank you!

Great customer service from everyone I interacted with, was my first time here and he really helped me figure out what I want and was knowledgeable on all the products. I was hesitant on getting one of the empanadas but I went for it and it was actually delicious taste homemade. Coffee was 7/10 taste like blonde espresso and I’m not a huge fan of blonde but the flavors were good I will definitely be back!!!
First time there today. OMG! Wish I went there sooner. I ordered a Mocha iced coffee and spinach feta pinwheel…so amazingly great!! I will be back soon!
Wow!  This place is great. Great coffee and friendly service.

Not only is the environment delightful and the service e courteous and timely, but the coffees are truly crafted with intention. Wow. The Colombian and Ethiopians pour overs were pleasant and fulfilling. It can be hard to pull the flavor notes out of the beams when the shop is busy. But Knowledge Perk delivers success in each cup. Yum. I’ll be back tomorrow.
You can taste the quality not only in the coffee but also the house made pastries. Just tried their new spinach, feta one and it was fantastic! Great space and baristas!

Wow!  GREAT coffee with very fresh beans that they roast themselves. They also have some very tasty treats to go with the coffee, including a gluten free chocolate torte that was out of this world. My husband has celiac,s and he has approved it too.
Great coffee and food!! Nice place to relax for a bit and hang out with family or friends to catch up.
My daughter and I enjoyed our orders. I had a pour-over coffee, and kudos to them for having heavy cream available. ✨️
Best place in the area.  Good coffee.  Good place to get some work done.

Amended review:
I've been coming here regularly since opening as it's in my backyard. I still love the coffee but the customer service has left the building. I used to be greeted, and given recommendations on flights, seasonal and other specials and now I'm lucky if I get acknowledged at the checkout. Not to mention it's winter yet I go inside and it's freezing. I'm not sure if the management has changed or what but does have me looking elsewhere to go for my afternoon meetings and coffee dates. Disappointed local.

Initial review:
Amazing location with great, friendly workers. I've been waiting for a place to work and hang out locally for a long time and I think I've found my spot. The bonus is the coffee experiences they offer throughout the week.
Delicious coffee, quick service when it’s busy, and they call you by name with a smile! Great addition to the Fort Mill / Tega Cay Community!

I love this place. The atmosphere is warm and inviting. I got so much work done. The coffee is great and the kindness of the owner is unlike anything I’ve experienced in Charlotte. You won’t be disappointed
Very nice servers. I liked my hot chocolate!
Delicious local coffee.
Locally owned and best coffee in town

It was a good ambiance. Our barista was helpful and knowledgeable Of menu items. Helped me make a decision on what coffee to order per my taste and likings. I found it slightly pricey. Next time I will be ordering their coffee flight. I also wish, if they were open late. I may not go to Starbucks then. Overall 3.95/5 stars.

This is my new favorite spot!! My two favorite right now is the hazelnut latte and the maple bourbon latte. The flavor is nice and subtle without overpowering the coffee flavor.  If you like overly sweet coffee drinks and burnt tasting coffee this place is not for you.

Moved to the area yesterday and mu coffee maker wasn't ready.  Found this GEM.  Everyone is so nice, incredibly helpful, and patient.  Helped me with something a little new and I loved it.  Perfect place for coffee meetings.  Pastries looked amazing as well!
Quick way to gain a customer is to be friendly.  Top notch service!
Coffee was fantastic and I loved the customer service!
Everything was amazing! The staff is always super nice and helpful! The breakfast empanadas are literally the best ever! Thank you!
Finally we found a place that offers all coffee (or at least the ones we like) as decaf! Super delicious drinks and cute place to come and hang out.
I didn’t like the drink I ordered and the barista was so so nice and remade it for me. Great food as well! Will definitely be back
Great experience, pleasant spot and the staff were very accommodating. So many great coffees to choose from!
Great coffee, tea and baked goods at KP's second location in the Fort Mill/Tega Cay area. All this coupled with friendly and attentive staff, that provide a welcoming atmosphere.
Great coffee and breakfast food.

I got the summer flight and was blown away by how refreshing each option I had was. The blackberry lemonade cold brew was absolutely perfect, and the chocolate orange one tasted like my favorite chocolate candy. Couldn’t have been better.

Nice place to meet for coffee or tea.
Manager gave our party free pastries to sample.
Very nice atmosphere, clearly planned and designed with care for a pleasant open/relaxed vibe. The coffee was okay.. planning to go back sometime and try some other simple drinks.
Interesting Coffee ☕
I got a mocha with hemp milk and cinnamon, my daughter got an egg and sausage Empanada, and my mom got a latte. All absolutely delicious and the staff was very friendly and quick.
Very comfortable

I was so excited to check this place out. This is my second visit the first being to the rock hill location and am dissapointed honestly. The staff is great and very kind but I ordered a cappuccino at both locations and got a latte at best. Maybe half an inch of foam both times 😭 and maybe the fort mill location is still training because the espresso was very bitter like it had sat too long before the milk and foam were added. Maybe this is just how they make cappuccinos or maybe both visits were just flukes but at $5 a pop plus tip I can't see myself going back.

Knowledge Perk is what Fort Mill needed. Locally owned and nothing is outsourced. Their original location is in Rock Hill - it is such a cool spot but I’m glad to have them right by me now! Give them a try, you won’t be disappointed.
Coffee is delicious, calm atmosphere, plenty of comfortable seating. Kids hot chocolate had perfect taste and temperature for the kids to immediately drink.
I love this place!!! So excited about the new location 🙌

raw_data.description:
Come relax in our beautiful café with indoor and outdoor seating. We offer freshly roasted coffee, cold brew, full range of expert espresso beverages, and a variety of sweet and savory pastries and bagel creations.

Thursday-Friday from 4:00pm-9:30pm, and Saturday from 6:00pm-9:30pm, we turn into Knowledge Perk "After Hours," serving coffee, original cocktails, beer, and wine.

We are a coffee roaster and beans are available onsite or via our website for retail purchase. We have immersive, engaging programs and events for our community to grow in their knowledge and enjoyment of coffee. Give us a call or visit our website for more information. Better yet, drop by to see us in person!
raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 1.5 hours here

posts.body:
💕 Love Is in the Air 💖
Join us after your special dinner for our Valentine's Date Night at Knowledge Perk After Hours!
We're doing a lot to celebrate! You can enjoy:
- Dessert Flights (Pick 4 from 8 varieties of cheesecakes and dessert bars) 🍰
- 2 New Cocktails (Strawberries & Cream Margarita, Mudslide Martini) 🍸
- Live Music from Jeremy Goodwyne (7:30pm - 10:30pm) 🎵
- Extended hours from 6:00pm - 11:00pm
- Chocolate Cherry Lattes

Coffee. Cocktails. Beer. Wine.

☕️🥃 Knowledge Perk After Hours is celebrating its grand opening this Saturday exclusively at Knowledge Perk Fort Mill! Our new After Hours concept is currently a KP Fort Mill exclusive, and after Saturday, its weekly hours to start will be Thursday-Saturday, 6:00pm - 9:30pm. Hours will likely expand in the future!

Enjoy our hand-picked selection of beer and wine, and our new line of original Knowledge Perk cocktails!

- The Menu -

Signature Espresso Martini:
Vodka, Burn Rate Espresso, Housemade Coffee Syrup

Café Old Fashioned:
Whiskey, Coffee Liqueur, Simple Syrup, Orange Bitters, Orange Peel

Pink Russian:
Vodka, Coffee Liqueur, Strawberry Vanilla Sweet Foam, Dried Strawberry, Chocolate Shavings

True Maple Bourbon Latte:
Whiskey, Burn Rate Espresso, Maple Syrup, Steamed Milk, Nutmeg

Vanilla Chai Sour:
Spiced Rum, Oregon Chai, Vanilla Syrup, Lime Juice, Nutmeg

Campfire:
Vanilla Vodka, Bourbon Cream Liqueur, Chocolate Sauce, Milk, Crushed Graham Cracker Rim, Torched Marshmallow

Cold Brew Creamsicle:
Vodka, Orange Triple Sec Liqueur, Fresh Squeezed Orange Juice, Cold Brew Coffee, Oat Milk, Vanilla Syrup, Orange Slice

Pumpkin Shake:
Vanilla Vodka, Bourbon Cream Liqueur, Half & Half, Pumpkin Puree, Pumpkin Pie Syrup, Whipped Cream, Blended, Espresso Optional

reviews_data.review_text: Great cup of coffee and quick service, I did go in the evening

reviews_data.review_text: Went there for their after hours event where they serve adult drinks. There was also music which was nice! Great place for impromptu date night.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review, Rob! We're glad you had a good time and hope you come back to see us again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: The coffee here is great, I recommend it. The employees are also very friendly. This is something we need in every business, especially food stores. The croissant is from somewhere else, the egg is from my kitchen. I just wanted the photo to look nice and appetizing. 🥰🤗

Knowledge Perk in Fort Mill is an absolute gem. The atmosphere is warm, welcoming, and just the right balance of calm and creative—perfect for getting work done or simply enjoying a moment of pause. I had the decaf lavender latte (extra hot), delicious. You can tell they care about the experience just as much as the coffee. Whether you’re working remotely or catching up with a friend, this is a go-to spot.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for this wonderful review, Lorelei! We hope to see you back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: We like this place very much. My kids always want hot chocolate from knowledge perk only.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're happy to hear your kids love our hot chocolate! We look forward to seeing you all back again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Visiting family out of town and have been trying local coffee shops. This place was by far the best stop! The staff were very friendly and helpful with questions on their menu. Their seasonal blueberry macchiato was amazing! Lots of seating space for small and large groups. If you are looking for a new place to try, stop by here you won’t regret it!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the great review, Steven! We hope you return the next time you're in town!

reviews_data.review_text: Always enjoy to try new coffee shop locations and this time my choice fell on this one since we were visiting the area. We ordered salmon bagel and two lattes. Salmon bagel had about 1% of salmon in it, 85% cream cheese and 14% was massive chunks of purple onions mix with cream cheese. I had a bad heartburn after it. I did ask not to put it there but they said it’s all pre made mix. Coffee tasted more like water and coffee than a coffee and milk. Overall 25$ down the drain. Won’t be coming back.

Our first time in the Fort Mill location and we were very disappointed. The atmosphere wasn't there for us like the one in Rock Hill. We didn't stay long because it was freezing in there. No wonder there was hardly anybody in there on a Friday night. They have it so cold that nobody wants to stay. A coffee shop is supposed to be cozy and relaxing, not feel like a freezer. Probably won't be back.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Dear Debbie,
We appreciate all feedback, even when it’s tough to hear. It’s unfortunate that your experience at our Fort Mill location didn’t meet your expectations, especially since you seemed to enjoy our Rock Hill shop. While we strive to create a comfortable atmosphere for all guests, we also recognize that temperature preferences can vary widely. Our team is always happy to adjust when concerns are brought to our attention during a visit. I’m very confident our team would’ve been very happy to adjust temperatures if requested. It was also 20° outside, and so we understand a hot cup of coffee would certainly add to the warmness as our heaters were likely working overtime. 

That said, we’ve noticed that your reviews tend to lean toward the negative, which makes us wonder if the issue is less about our coffee shop and more about your approach to customer experiences. We take great pride in what we do, and while we may not be the right fit for everyone, we are confident in the warm and welcoming environment we provide to thousands of happy guests. I’m not sure a one star review in this case is extremely warranted, nor is it fair to us as a small business when we do a phenomenal job in so many other areas on a very consistent basis. 

If you’d like to give us another try, we’d love the opportunity to change your mind. If not, we sincerely hope you find a coffee shop that better aligns with your preferences and temperature.

Wishing you all the best,
Ryan.

The service was just alright, the baristas were not overly friendly and the girl working the counter was more interested in her friend that was there. I’d go back and get a coffee again, but I’d skip the bagel.
Great friendly service and nice atmosphere but unfortunately one of the worst lattes I’ve had around here. Borderline undrinkable
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Ahmad, thanks for visiting our café and leaving your feedback! We appreciate the kind words about our team's customer service. The latte in that photo does not meet our standards of quality and should not have been served with that much foam. We will definitely address this with our team. We apologize for your experience and hope you will give us another chance! Please send an email to fortmillgm@knowledgeperk.com so that we can make it right!

reviews_data.review_text: The coffee is great and they have incredibly comfortable chairs. Great place to hang out and get some work done.

reviews_data.review_text: I live next to this place and wanted so badly to like it, but they didn’t have vanilla, they didn’t have oat-milk (two starter pack ingredients for a coffee shop) and they forgot to make my bagel sandwich until my husband went to ask about it 10 minutes later.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for review and your feedback. We're sorry your experience didn't meet our standards of service. You unfortunately caught us on a bad day where we had some delivery issues. We do normally always have vanilla and oat milk in stock. We'd love to have you come back and give us another try. Your next vanilla oat milk latte is on us!

reviews_data.review_text: I purchased a tea which was $3.21 for a small. Which is a bit pricey I can get a whole box of tea for close to that price. . I'm not a cheapskate and I don't mind shelling out money for things I like but Dunkin Dounuts is half the price same size.  Also when I looked inside the tea it was not in a tea bag it was tea loose. This is not safe if your giving tea to a kids or the elderly they can digest the loose tea particles and choke..  I think customers should be warned of this type of brewing process.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Nora, thank you for your review and your feedback! Our tea, though loose leaf, is supposed to be properly strained and there should not be loose floating tea at the bottom of your cup. We apologize for this mistake and hope you come back to give us another chance! We would like to make this right to you, so shoot us an email at infofm@knowledgeperk.com and your next drink is on us!

reviews_data.review_text: The diced bagel sandwiches are incredible!

reviews_data.review_text: I like this place for a couple of reasons. They use different beans from all over the world. They have heavy cream as an option, where most only have half & half. reviews_data.review_text: This is the only place where they get the flat white right every single time, no matter who the barista is. Finding such consistent, great service is incredibly rare. It also offers a wonderful atmosphere for focusing."

reviews_data.review_text: KP has the best coffee in town! Their seasonal drink menu doesn't disappoint. The baristas are super friendly. Also, Mexico Villareal whole coffee beans FOR LIFE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Seriously good stuff!

reviews_data.review_text:
I visit occasionally to catch up with a friend. We like their coffee and it's a relatively quiet place. You get a lot of street traffic noise if you sit outside. Inside is better obviously, to avoid that.

No matter what coffee you get they are usually right on the money. Also they roast their own beans at their Rock Hill location.

They have a limited amount of snacks in display case by the register and only occasionally have I ever see something that might be gluten free. So if that's you thing plan on the possibility of not having something to eat.

The furniture is ok for the most part. But the center island of stools are, to me anyway, awkward and very uncomfortable. But to be fair these are a leftover from the prior business that was there.

Stop by and have a cup, all in all it's a solid choice.
Amazing place, love the spinach feta with my coffee. #TYG #lifeisgood

reviews_data.review_text:

reviews_data.review_text: Really good coffee.  Cinnamon buns were really good.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Josh!

reviews_data.review_text: The flat white was wonderful. Very relaxing and chill environment

reviews_data.review_text: Beautiful place with more perfect coffee!!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee shop
Spectacular food and service. Ordered breakfast and was delicious. Ciarra was awesome.
Did not have the advertised food.

First time experience. I showed up around 9am and ordered a Toffee Crunch latte. The baristas were friendly and my drink was made quickly. I brought my laptop as I had planned to stay and work. The shop was packed however, and the music was loud which isn’t conducive for working. The middle bar/island seating barstools are weird. They swing in/out and it’s very easy to lose your balance and slip as I did along with 2 other women who were sitting down across from me at the same time. The latte was underwhelming and was missing the rich espresso flavor I like. It tasted more like watered down coffee with flavored syrup and foam. I’m gonna stick to the Starbucks rivers and lakes I’m used to.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the review and the kind words about our team, Brittany!  We have adjusted music levels to hopefully a better level, and we acknowledge the stools... We do have plans to replace all those, they are a carry over from the original store and we are looking forward to updating them with real chairs soon! I hate that you didn't enjoy your latte, we'd love for you to come try us again.  As a small batch roaster, our espresso is a little lighter than some of the chain stores and so it can be harder to taste through the latte that has a sweeter syrup like the toffee crunch. That being said, we would love to help you find something that showcases our great espresso a little more, and we would welcome the chance to serve you again with hopefully a more positive experience! Either way, thanks for giving us a chance, we are grateful for every opportunity to earn a new customers business. Ryan

Coffee is delicious, calm atmosphere, plenty of comfortable seating. Kids hot chocolate had perfect taste and temperature for the kids to immediately drink.
